                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.5151/946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-04T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. For Cochran from the Secretary of the Treasury. Please inform Minister of
                    Finance Auriol that you have been instructed by your government to inform him
                    that we would prefer that draft document mentioned in cable 831 be presented
                    simultaneously to both treasuries and in the case of the United States be
                    transmitted through you. For your information and guidance please bear in mind
                    that Monday September 7 is Labor Day and on Tuesday September 8 United States
                    Treasury is offering to the public a 900,000,000 dollar bond issue. Keep me
                    informed by cable or telephone if necessary on any developments.
                    [Morgenthau.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
